name: Shipgirls
description:
FOR SOME REASON HAS A TENDENCY TO MAKE WEIRD BACKGROUNDS.

The background issue has been solved V2. The success rate still depends on the model.

Tried making it possible to make different nations. So far the best results are with with Iron Blood and Northern Parliament. They use either IronBlood or NorthernParliament activation tags too.

Though, I feel like in general using the lora became harder.

Definitely has room for improvement. I'll spend some time working on this lora until I think it's good enough.

Well...I've been browsing through the Azur Lane section, feeling despair as everything was already made and I did not know where to put my time. What to train. So...I decided to f that all and jus made shipgirls lora. Not the easiest one to use, I think. I'm not sure. The results are mostly fine. I didn't test with other loras or with extremely long prompts.

Example images are made with MeinaHentai and Anything 4.5 - haven't tried AbyssOrange, Pastel, and Cetus but I think Cetus would most likely work nicely too.

Very important for the best results - OpenPose standing poses. But they are not 100% required.

Weight I use - either 1 or 1.1

For a simple shipgirl I use tags like - shipgirl, 1girl, rigging, turret, solo, looking at viewer, full body,

The Iron Blood girls with their weapons use less typical rigging and more their robotic mechanic whatever.

When making those I suggest something like this:

For a simple shipgirl I use tags like - shipgirl, IronBlood, rigging, turret, 1girl, non-humanoid robot, solo, looking at viewer, full body,

Wide resolution makes the guns larges, while your typical portrait resolution makes them look simpler.
